
[1]pavement

   PA'VEMENT, n. [L. pavimentum.] A floor or covering consisting of stones
   or bricks, laid on the earth in such a manner as to make a hard and
   convenient passage; as a pavement of pebbles, of bricks, or of marble.

   PA'VEMENT, v.t. To pave; to floor with stone or brick. [Unusual.]
